msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
#. VAR: Ovādavagga → ­bhik­khu­nū­passa­ya­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 23"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:0.5"
msgid "23. Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on nuns’ dwelling places"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.56, pts-cs-bu-pc23.1, pts-vp-en.2.276, ms2V_531
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country at Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovadanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six went to the nuns’ dwelling place and instructed the nuns from the group of six."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the nuns said to the nuns from the group of six,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.4"
msgid "“ethāyye, ovādaṃ gamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerables, let’s go to the instruction.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Yampi → yaṃ hi (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.5"
msgid "“Yampi mayaṃ, ayye, gaccheyyāma ovādassa kāraṇā, ayyā chabbaggiyā idheva āgantvā amhe ovadantī”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no need; the monks from the group of six came and instructed us right here.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The nuns complained and criticized the monks from the group of six,"

#. VAR: chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti → chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ na gacchissantīti (bj) | chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ­bhik­khu­nū­passa­yaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadantīti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six go and instruct the nuns at their dwelling place?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And those nuns told the monks."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_532
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.9"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.10"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.11"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six go and instruct the nuns at their dwelling place?”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.12"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.13"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.14"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.15"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you go and instruct the nuns at their dwelling place?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.16"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.17"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.17a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_533
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.18"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk goes to a nun’s dwelling place, and then instructs her, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_534
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:1.19"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-pc23.2, pts-vp-en.2.277, ms2V_535
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena mahāpajāpati gotamī gilānā hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards Mahāpajāpati Gotamī became sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.2"
msgid "Therā bhikkhū yena mahāpajāpati gotamī tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "The senior monks went to see her"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavocuṃ—“"
msgstr "and said,"

#. VAR: kacci → kacci te (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.4"
msgid "kacci, gotami, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?"
msgstr "“We hope you’re bearing up, Gotamī, we hope you’re getting better?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.5"
msgid "“Na me, ayyā, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ”."
msgstr "“I’m not bearing up, Venerables, and I’m not getting better."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.6"
msgid "“Iṅghayyā, dhammaṃ desethā”ti."
msgstr "Please give me a teaching.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.7"
msgid "“Na, bhagini, kappati bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo dhammaṃ desetun”ti kukkuccāyantā na desesuṃ."
msgstr "“It’s not allowable for us to go and teach a nun at her dwelling place.” And being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not teach her."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena mahāpajāpati gotamī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards, the Master robed up in the morning, took his bowl and robe, and went to Mahāpajāpati Gotamī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.10"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And he said to her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.11"
msgid "“kacci, gotami, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?"
msgstr "“I hope you’re bearing up, Gotamī, I hope you’re getting better?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.12"
msgid "“Pubbe me, bhante, therā bhikkhū āgantvā dhammaṃ desenti."
msgstr "“Previously, Venerable Sir, the senior monks would come and teach me,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.13"
msgid "Tena me phāsu hoti."
msgstr "and because of that I would be comfortable."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.14"
msgid "Idāni pana—‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti, kukkuccāyantā na desenti."
msgstr "But now they don’t teach because they’re afraid of wrongdoing, saying, ‘It’s been prohibited by the Master.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.15"
msgid "Tena me na phāsu hotī”ti."
msgstr "And because of that I’m not comfortable.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.16"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr "After instructing, inspiring, and gladdening her with a teaching, the Master rose from his seat and departed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.17"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.18"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā gilānaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ovadituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to go and instruct a sick nun at her dwelling place."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.19"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: bhikkhunupassayaṃ → bhik­khu­nū­passa­yaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-pli4.57, ms2V_536
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.20"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk goes to the nuns’ dwelling place and then instructs them, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:2.21"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānā hoti bhikkhunī—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is that a nun is sick.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc23.3.1, ms2V_537
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-en.2.278, ms2V_538
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunupassayo nāma"
msgstr "The nuns’ dwelling place:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.7"
msgid "yattha bhikkhuniyo ekarattampi vasanti."
msgstr "where nuns stay for even a single night."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_539
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.8"
msgid "Upasaṅkamitvāti"
msgstr "Goes to:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.9"
msgid "tattha gantvā."
msgstr "goes there."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_540
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.10"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "Them:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.11"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "they have been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_541
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.12"
msgid "Ovadeyyāti"
msgstr "Instructs:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.13"
msgid "aṭṭhahi garudhammehi ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he instructs about the eight rules to be respected, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_542
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.14"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.15"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_543
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.16"
msgid "Gilānā nāma"
msgstr "A sick nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: A formal meeting of the community,” _saṃvāsa_, is defined at _pācittiya_ 69, [](MS.2.1274), as the observance day ceremony, the invitation ceremony, or a procedure.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.1.17"
msgid "bhikkhunī na sakkoti ovādāya vā saṃvāsāya vā gantuṃ."
msgstr "she is not able to go to the instruction or to a formal meeting of the community."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14, pts-cs-bu-pc23.3.2, ms2V_544
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.1"
msgid "Upasampannāya upasampannasaññī bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is fully ordained, and he perceives her as fully ordained, and he goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.2"
msgid "Upasampannāya vematiko bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is fully ordained, but he is unsure if she is, and he goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.3"
msgid "Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññī bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is fully ordained, but he perceives her as not fully ordained, and he goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_545
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.4"
msgid "Aññena dhammena ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he instructs her with another teaching, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.5"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is not fully ordained, but he perceives her as fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampannāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If she is not fully ordained, and he perceives her as not fully ordained, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc16, pts-cs-bu-pc23.3.3, ms2V_546
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.3"
msgid "uddesaṃ dento,"
msgstr "if he gives a summary;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.4"
msgid "paripucchaṃ dento,"
msgstr "if he questions them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.5"
msgid "“osārehi ayyā”ti vuccamāno osāreti,"
msgstr "if he recites when asked to do so;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.6"
msgid "pañhaṃ pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.7"
msgid "pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,"
msgstr "if he replies when asked a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.8"
msgid "aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ bhikkhuniyo suṇanti,"
msgstr "if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.9"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is to a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.10"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is to a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.11"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.12"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. VAR: Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpadaṃ → bhik­khu­nū­passa­ya­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
#. REF: sc17, ms2V_547,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:3.3.13"
msgid "Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The third rule, the training rule on nuns’ dwelling places, is finished."
